The paper discusses a novel approach to analyzing multi-source data using multilayered networks, which involves identifying features of a central event and proposing a network layer for each feature. This approach allows for independent study of each feature and its impact on the event, as well as composition of features in arbitrary ways for aggregate impacts and "what if" scenarios. This suggests that the paper could fit into several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DB (Databases), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
